# Auto push to GitHub

When you finish a task that changes project code in this repo:

1. Commit only relevant files (never `.env`, secrets, `backup/`, `*.backup*`, `_patch_*.py` unless the user asked).
2. Use a concise commit message in the repo style (why-focused, 1–2 sentences).
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (usually `main`): `git push origin HEAD`.
4. Tell the user the commit hash and that Streamlit Cloud will redeploy from the push (may take 1–3 minutes; Reboot app only if deploy seems stuck or secrets changed).

Do not ask "should I push?" unless the push fails (auth, conflict) or the user said not to push in that message.

If there are no code changes to commit, skip commit/push.
